The paper deals with the problem of estimating aggregate query answers over hidden web databases, which involves techniques from database systems (cs.DB), information retrieval (cs.IR), and web search (cs.WEB). The paper also proposes algorithms for tracking aggregates over dynamic web databases, which involves techniques from data structures (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
